title: Allegations about Farage’s conduct as schoolboy ‘disturbing’, says No 10 – UK politics live
summary: The Guardian interviewed over a dozen of Nigel Farage's former classmates from Dulwich College, a prestigious public school in South London. These conversations aimed to shed light on Farage's early life and personality. Insights into his character and formative experiences were revealed through these discussions.

title: Daniel Radcliffe writes supportive letter to Harry Potter successor in new TV series
summary: The actor expressed his hopes for 11-year-old Dominic McLaughlin, wishing him an even better experience growing up in the role than he himself had. He emphasized the positive aspects of the journey in the role. The message reflects support and encouragement for the young actor.

title: Death toll from Russian attack rises to 25 as Ukraine says it will raise issue at UN – Europe live
summary: Ukraine will address the recent overnight attack on Ternopil, which resulted in over 70 injuries, during an upcoming security council meeting. The government aims to discuss the implications and response to the incident. This highlights ongoing security concerns amid the ongoing conflict in the region.

title: EU executive draws up plan for greater mobility of armed forces in Europe
summary: The European Commission is proposing to simplify regulations for cross-border movements within the EU to establish a 'military Schengen' zone. This initiative aims to enhance cooperation and mobility among member states in military contexts. The goal is to streamline processes and improve operational efficiency for defense forces across Europe.

title: Arsenal’s controversial sponsorship deal with Visit Rwanda to end next year
summary: Rwanda faces backlash for its support of the M23 militia, which is involved in ongoing conflicts in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The situation has raised tensions in the region. Critics are calling for accountability and a reassessment of Rwanda's actions.
